            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, heat a separate large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>coated pork</strong> and cook for 5-6 min on each side or until golden and cooked through (no pink meat!) – this is your <strong>chilli & fennel pork scaloppine</strong></p><p>Once cooked through, transfer the <strong>chilli & fennel pork scaloppine[s]</strong> to a clean plate to rest</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1698222515189-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1698222515189-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1698222515189-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1698222515189-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1698222515189-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the pork is cooking, dissolve your <strong>chicken stock mix</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> in 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[225ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[300ml] </span><strong>boiled water </strong>– this is your <strong>chicken stock</strong></p><p>Drain and rinse your <strong>cannellini beans</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1698222519566-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1698222519566-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1698222519566-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1698222519566-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1698222519566-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the leek has softened, add the <strong>sliced</strong> <strong>shallot</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> to the pan and cook for 2-3 min or until lightly golden</p><p>Once lightly golden, add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>garlic</strong> and <strong>remaining fennel seeds</strong></p><p>Cook for 1 min or until fragrant, then add the <strong>drained beans</strong> and <strong>chicken stock</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat, then reduce the heat to medium and cook for 5-6 min or until the sauce has reduced by half – this is your <strong>bean stew</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1698222525098-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1698222525098-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1698222525098-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1698222525098-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1698222525098-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the sauce has thickened, reduce the heat to low and add your <strong>crème fraîche</strong></p><p>Gently stir it all together and cook for a final 1-2 min or until warmed through (don’t let it boil!) – this is your <strong>creamy bean stew</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1698222528693-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1698222528693-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1698222528693-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1698222528693-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1698222528693-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>creamy bean stew</strong> topped with the <strong>chilli & fennel pork scaloppine</strong> and the <strong>salad</strong></p><p>Add a small drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong>, season generously with <strong>black pepper</strong> and sprinkle over the <strong>remaining chilli flakes </strong>(not a fan of spice? Just add a little!)</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
